# Status Model

Use these statuses for requirements, scenarios, use cases, and traceability rows.

| Status | Meaning |
|---|---|
| Draft | A first version exists. |
| Needs Clarification | Ambiguities block implementation. |
| Domain Reviewed | The domain model was reviewed. |
| Architecture Reviewed | Technical solution and ADRs were reviewed. |
| Ready for Dev | Implementation can start. |
| In Dev | Implementation is in progress. |
| In Review | Change is ready for review. |
| Verified | Tests, contracts, or acceptance criteria pass. |
| Released | Available to users or the target environment. |
| Deprecated | Requirement or scenario was retired. |
